OBJECTIVE:
Before you can access the main ship systems, you must complete the
emergency orientation protocol. This will verify your terminal access
and familiarize you with the ship's computer interface.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASK 1: Crew Manifest Verification
──────────────────────────────────
The crew manifest is stored in this directory. Read the file 'manifest.txt'
to see the crew roster. Count the total number of crew members.

Then, create a file called 'crew_count.txt' containing ONLY the number.

Example: If there are 15 crew members, the file should contain just: 15

VERIFICATION:
When you've created the file correctly, run:
    ./verify

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

HINTS:
• Use 'cat manifest.txt' to view the crew list
• Use 'wc -l manifest.txt' to count lines in a file
• Use 'echo 24 > crew_count.txt' to create a file with a number
  (replace 24 with the actual count)

AVAILABLE FILES:
• manifest.txt    - Crew roster
• verify          - Verification script (run when ready)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

When this task is complete, proceed to the equipment check:
    cd equipment_bay

